cs.DL, cs.CR, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.SE 

This paper focuses on open-source software solutions for digital preservation repositories, which involves aspects of digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of security and protocols in digital preservation, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper also touches upon the dynamic of development and open-source licensing, which is relevant to software engineering (cs.SE).
